They also have a really neat set-up for outdoor dining.We dined outside in like 20 degree weather and felt no cold thanks to the little greenhouses they have with heaters. It’s really nice to see restaurants be innovative during such difficult times. I will happily continue to support and recommend! P.S. the margaritas are 😎

The service needs some revamping done. While there, I felt like I saw an uneven distrubtion of work amongst the staff which led to a less than great dining experience. Maybe people usually don't mind because the food and drinks were pretty good. The drinks were strong and tasty and the food was well made.

Met some friends for lunch there yesterday and look forward to returning. Food was great, atmosphere was super chill and their COVID precautions were great. As a heads up, they are cash only, but there is an ATM in the restaurant and there is no fee to use it. There are also super cute little houses outside for maybe a party if 4. Super cute, it was just a little chilly so we opted for inside.  Covid Measures: Temp taken at check in, all staff wear a mask, disposable utensils are provided, there are plastic dividers up between all tables inside and out.  Food & Bev: Very very happy overall. Two of us got the tortilla soup and it was SO good. Two of us also got the burrito bowl - also super yum! The portion size was so big that we both took our leftovers home. We also got the mini nachos which was a great starter. Margaritas were also really tasty. We appreciated they don't use marg mix and rather use fresh like juice. They also have a great happy hour! $4 draft beers and specials on many other drinks.  Overall, great experience. They weren't too busy, which was a bummer since we had such a nice, chill time. Go bring them some business!! 😊🌮🍻
Get the carnitas nachos! And a guava margarita.

Oh my vegan dishes! Recently, I’ve switched to eating more plant based and I’m always tempted to not stick to my diet when going out. Not at El Santo! They have a whole selection just of vegan Mexican food. I got the vegan enchiladas, and the sauce is what dreams are made of. Paired with a smoked papaya margarita, incredible! Even the french fries were too good not to order a second round. 10 out of 10 would recommend.
Frozen drinks were small, but delicious. We ordered nachos, as you apparently can't just order drinks, you're required to order food as well. Just a heads up, they only accept cash or Venmo.

OMG I am so glad my daughter found this place.  Talk about fabulous, the food was amazing. We had nachos and I was surprised that the meat was inside the chips. There was no issues with the food. The issue was with delivery ,he left my food at my security desk (they don't watch deliveries) and I told him to call when he was on the way..he didn't. Thats why its 4 stars. We will be ordering again and again.

I am extremely disappointed with the service I received at this place.  It was a Saturday night and there was a nice crowd of people, but not too many people to excuse the waitress for her poor service. My mom, sister and I waited a good 20 minutes to be tended to, and in that time a couple of Caucasian women came in and were seated next to us. As we were still waiting to be tended to, the Caucasian women who had just arrived, got their drinks and order taken within 5 minutes of being seated. Now, i'm not a racist but it was very shameful to have been sitting in a Latin restaurant, being Latin myself yet treated like i'm a second class citizen or something.  For the record, not I or my family members will patronize this place ever! i'm completely disgusted.
